<ansi fg="yellow-bold">config</ansi> - Configure game systems

<ansi fg="cyan">Usage:</ansi>
  config                           - Show available configuration categories
  config combat                    - Show combat configuration options
  config combat info               - Show current combat settings
  config combat system <name>      - Switch combat system
  config combat systems            - List available combat systems
  config combat <setting> <value>  - Change a combat setting

<ansi fg="cyan">Description:</ansi>
  Allows administrators to configure various game systems at runtime.
  Currently supports combat system configuration.

<ansi fg="cyan">Combat Player Settings (Twitch Only):</ansi>
  unarmed_base_ms     - Base cooldown for unarmed combat (milliseconds)
  armed_base_ms       - Base cooldown for armed combat (milliseconds)
  max_speed_reduction - Maximum speed reduction percentage (0-100)
  speed_divisor       - Divisor for speed bonus calculation

<ansi fg="cyan">Combat Mob Settings (Twitch Only):</ansi>
  mob_unarmed_base_ms     - Base cooldown for mob unarmed combat
  mob_armed_base_ms       - Base cooldown for mob armed combat
  mob_max_speed_reduction - Maximum speed reduction for mobs
  mob_speed_divisor       - Divisor for mob speed bonus

<ansi fg="cyan">Examples:</ansi>
  config                               - List config categories
  config combat                        - Show combat config options
  config combat info                   - View current settings
  config combat systems                - List available combat systems
  config combat system combat-twitch   - Switch to twitch combat
  config combat unarmed_base_ms 3000   - Set player unarmed to 3 seconds
  config combat mob_unarmed_base_ms 4000 - Set mob unarmed to 4 seconds

<ansi fg="cyan">Note:</ansi>
  This is an admin-only command. Changes to combat settings are
  saved to the main configuration file and persist across restarts.

<ansi fg="yellow">See Also:</ansi> combatinfo, server